problem_text: [BG] Some mammals have teeth. Platypus have no teeth. Platypus are mammals. Humans have teeth.
predicates:
Mammal(x) ::: x is a mammal.
HasTeeth(x) ::: x has teeth.
Platypus(x) ::: x is a platypus.
Human(x) ::: x is a human.

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? All humans have teeth.
Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? No platypus is a human.
tests.conclusions: ¬∃x (Platypus(x) ∧ Human(x)) ::: No platypus is a human. TRUE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Some mammals are platypuses that do not have teeth.
tests.conclusions: ∃x (Mammal(x) ∧ Platypus(x) ∧ ¬HasTeeth(x)) ::: Some mammals are platypuses that do not have teeth. TRUE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? All mammals are humans or platypuses.
Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? If a mammal has teeth, then it is not a platypus.
Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Some mammals are humans that have teeth.
Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? All mammals that do not have teeth are platypuses.
Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? If a mammal is a human, then it has teeth.
Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? All humans are mammals that have teeth.
Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? If a mammal is a platypus, then it does not have teeth.
